<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Feeder Foot" class="currentChild" href="Feeder_Foot">Feeder Foot</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An adjustable device attached to the rear of a sheetfed press's <a title="Feeder Section" href="Feeder_Section">feeder section</a> used to set the correct height of the paper pile to ensure proper feeding into the press. It also contains a nozzle that blows a jet of air beneath the topmost sheet lifted by the <a title="Pickup Sucker" href="Pickup_Sucker">pickup sucker</a>s. (See <a title="Feeder Section: Sheetfed Offset Lithography" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Feeder_Section:_Sheetfed_Offset_Lithography">Feeder Section: Sheetfed Offset Lithography</a> and <a title="Sheet Separation Unit" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Sheet_Separation_Unit">Sheet Separation Unit</a>.) The feeder foot is also called a <a title="Pressure Foot" href="Pressure_Foot">pressure foot</a>. 
</p>
